# Gamma configuration — copy to .env and edit.
# docker-compose loads this automatically; for bare-metal: set -a; source .env

# --- First-run admin account (optional). A FRESH instance (no accounts yet)
#     seeds its own first admin at startup: "admin" with a RANDOM password
#     printed once to the server log (docker logs <container>). Set these to
#     pick the name/password for that one-time seed instead. Once any account
#     exists these are ignored, so names/passwords/privileges you manage in
#     the GUI (account menu -> "Manage users...") are never touched.
#     Forgot the password? Recover with:
#       docker exec <container> python manage.py set-password <user> <new>
#GAMMA_ADMIN_USER=admin
#GAMMA_ADMIN_PASSWORD=change-me

# --- AI defaults (optional) ---
# AI is configured in the app, not here: each user adds provider entries under
# account menu → "AI providers & keys…" (API format + key + optional label,
# base URL, and model list). Keys are stored server-side per user and never
# sent back to the browser. The variables below only change the per-protocol
# default base URL offered in that dialog:
#   anthropic — Anthropic Messages API; also works with DeepSeek, Kimi, GLM, ...
#   openai    — OpenAI Chat Completions API; also works with OpenAI-compatible servers
#GAMMA_AI_ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL=https://api.anthropic.com
#GAMMA_AI_OPENAI_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com

# Legacy key/model variables (GAMMA_AI_*_API_KEY, GAMMA_AI_API_KEY,
# ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN, GAMMA_AI_MODELS, GAMMA_AI_MODEL, GAMMA_AI_PROVIDER)
# are ignored — providers are per-user, managed in the GUI.
